<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9896029153194></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9896029153194><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=9896029153194>RE: Bards twist 3-4</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=9896029153194#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, May 11th 1:41 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have great connection and a powerful computer and this has been instrumental in my song twisting.&nbsp;&nbsp;Lag is the daeth of bards.  Trun off your particle affect, setup hot keys for your songs so they can start and stop and start two songs with one key.  You will have to work with it to get the timing down right but it can be done.  I have twisted up to 5 songs with out losing my songs affect, but it was only to prove I can do it and would not attempted to do it during play.  My normal song twisting in outside areas are 2 to three songs.  In dungeon, cities, caves, or any inside area I normally twist three songs to buff the pary and one to hinder the MOB.  Also remember, Practice does make perfect.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
