<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98950579275933></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98950579275933><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=98950579275933>RE: Bards twist 3-4</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=98950579275933#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, May 10th 10:43 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have never been able to twist four songs without the first one losing effect for at least a econd or so. Based on the timing of most song, (3seconds to start a song, nine secoonds of play after it is stopped) I don't think it is possible to continuously twist four or five songs. Unless you don't mind losing the effect of at least one of them. <br><br>Three effects can be very effective. if you choose the right songs. I am a level 31 bard and have never had any complaints. Don't be afraid to try new combinations...or to change your stratagy with different mobs and different situations.&nbsp;&nbsp;=)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
