	   <tr><td colspan=2>The mask of deception drops off the ghoul assassin in Lower Guk as our anonymous friend mentioned.&nbsp;&nbsp;Since it is a rogue/bard only item most parties will let you loot it.  If you don't kill any froglok's then they will leave you alone in Upper Guk.  In Lower Guk you will need a good set of maps, at least two doses of invisibility from undead, and a little luck (Note that the gargoyles, bats, and spiders CAN see you).  You can zone over near the bedroom (it is the only dry zone over to Lower Guk).  Make sure to avoid the gargoyles and bats near the assassin's room because they will see you and eat you for breakfast. My recommendation is to zone over to Lower Guk and shout out "Is anyone camping the Assassin's room?"  if you get a response then ask if you can be on the list for the next drop of the mask (make sure to be nice about it they do not have to give it to you). Log as that character and relog with another one.  Let them send you a tell when it drops and relog with your bard/rogue. Run to get the item and grab this cool item.  It is +13 charisma +7 Save Magic AC4 illusion as dark elf (if cast) and gives you ultravision.  Good luck  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
