	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hey all, hoped you liked my last post on why to be a bard. I've been developing a nice method over the past couple of months. People area always asking me if it's worth fighting with instruments bellow lvl 40 (when u start getting hyped instruments from planes & etc). I can tell you, it is. Grasshoper,take a seat, stare at this rock, contemplate, and let me instruct you on my "5 animal form" of bard instrument fighting. first thing to do, attain decent instruments (we're talking lutes and brass horns). A nice instrument to get, lute wise, is the Lute of Gypsy Princess, purchased off a fellow bard (if he aint too greedy, for about 300-400pp), or go to Mistmoore and find a VERY nice uber to help u attain one. It adds a bit of haste to your string skills, and the no-drop one has +5sv magic &lt;shrug&gt;. Once you have these weapons, set up a new hotbutton page. First button we want to set up for "Denons Disrupt", and the second for "Chords of Dissonance". Third button, set up for either Brusco Bellow (to interrupt pesky castors), "Chain" song, or "Siren" song. 4th button, mebe something like "Disenchant", or any of the above. 5th button, set up for your 2nd hand melee, from your char inventory by holding the left mouse on it. 6th button, have an open slot in your inventory w/ no backpack, and hotkey that space in the 6th button. Now, grasshoper, you are doing well (BTW, print this, makes it easier). Alright, take your first instrument (make it brass, for later), and put it in your 2nd melee slot. Then 2nd instrument (string)and put it in the space u reserved for the 6th hotbutton (see previous mention). You will see both instruments have shown up in the hotbutton slots. Neat, huh? Now, I see, you are getting the idea! This makes it soooo much easier to switch instruments back & forth, as well as pressing the hotbutton #'s. Now, got to an easy area for testing, my student. Assuming your hotkey menu is open that we just set up, and your brass in hand, press 1, watch your hands light up for Denons. BTW, try to do this w/ just 1 enemy around (cause of the AoE). Your enemy will get hit, and go aggro on u. Quick, click on your lute in the 6th slot, move it a hair, bredth to the 5th slot (where the brass is), and replace it. SO EASY, NO?! Then, quickly tap 2 twice, to initialize Chords. Also, attack him at same time (I HAVE ASSUMED YOU'VE PRACTICED H2H COMBAT!!). Go back and forth with your instrument attacks, and watch your enemy fall. Try this on harder enemies, watch how effective this is. It gets even better the higher you go, because the effects of these songs get stronger, and the instruments double their effectiveness, almost exactly like hitting with a good weapon! Try this out, tell me what you think. I have been using it for a few lvls now, and it's REALLY effective. It helps groups out too, for crowd control when you get a few mobs that start spreading out to unwanted areas, like Castors, etc. Hope you are please, send me an email if you are satisfied. I have a few more pointers that I could divulge into. My email is gblog@swbell.net. Be well, my friends.<br>Sincerely,<br><br>Sehtlobo D'Anica<br>Drinal Server<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
