	   <tr><td colspan=2>This is great advice.&nbsp;&nbsp;I've been doing somehting similar, but was not sure if it was the most effective way to exchange melee items.<br><br>I have set up a hot-box - call it n, where n, m = 1 through 6.  So, in hot-box, n, I have put copies of my PRImary melee slot, SECondary melee slot, and General inventory Slot(s) 3, 4, 7 & 8.  Right-hand and left-hand weapons/shields go into slots 3 & 4 respectively, and instruments to be kept "close-to-hand"  ;-)  go into slots 7 & 8.<br><br>I keep another hot-box, m, with copies of social macros for twisting 3 songs; hot-box m slot 0 (10th slot) is for /stopsong. I just use alt-#, where # = 1-8 of spell/song gem slots, to twist in songs individually.  [BTW, I generally group songs into twisting macros by casting skill required (singing, percussion, string, etc) or by desired series of effects (buff and heal, buff and damage, etc)- any comments, anyone?].  {BTW, using social macros to twist songs has been explained by other, more illustrious bards, in this forum.}<br><br>One can switch between hot-boxes by shift-n, shift-m, etc.<br><br>Thank you for confirming that this method is correct for swapping melee items.  But does anyone know of a more effective way, so that one can swap items *without* mouse clicks?<br><br>Keep entertaining, keep posting, and melee on!<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>---<br>Tuneful Regards,<br>Caeleric, a Half Elf Bard of Erolissi Marr on Povar</td></tr>
