<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98946920363910></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98946920363910><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=98946920363910>There's something that needs to be corrected.</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=98946920363910#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=20485><span id= >LeOde</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>5 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, May 10th 12:33 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I would like to point out that your conclusion needs some clarification.<br><br>a) Grouping with people of a higher level is good. It's even better if you get xp.<br><br>b) I understand what you are trying to say - but you DO NOT get the same xp if he were your level.<br><br>Let me explain: If you are lv 40 and he is lv 60 and he kills a lv 49 mob. Your bar moves a good deal... his hardly moves. The reason of course is that the lv 60 is in ubber hell.<br><br>a lv 49 mob should give about 180 thousand xp.. more if it's a dungeon mob. Of that 180 thousand... about 1/8th of that will go to you (because you have about 100 million xp and the lv 60 should have at least 800 million)..<br><br>BUT - if you were grouped with a lv 40, and the two of you killed a lv 49 (this is riddicoulously hard to do BTW) then you each recieve half! or almost 5 times as much xp.<br><br>This is a technicallity really, and the original point you were trying to put accross is that people should never be afraid to group up with others who are higher level (as long as you can still get xp).<br><br><br>Take it from a bard who regularly groups with people 10 to 15 levels above my own level... it's good! (hehe - Bards are about the only class who can get away with being in Karnors at lv 40!)<br><br><br>Here's some really useful info: To find out if you will get xp if you join a group.. take the level of the highest member and multiply it by 2/3rds... if your levl is that or higher - then you will get xp. Please note that this only applies after level 20. Before level 20, the limit is 4 levels.<br><br><br><br>LeOde, of Lanys T'Vyl<br>Bard of the 43rd song<br>Proud un-twinked owner of SS Boots and Gauntlets!<br>Eager awaiter of the Planes.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>--Le Ode of Lanys T'Vyl</td></tr>
